rComments: Very enthusiastic and enjoys what she teaches with a passion which asserts her class to be enthusiastic and care about what we are learning in class. She is very kind and always available to help her students in succeeding in the class. CITB04 was a class that I learned so much from and I believe all profs should be like her.

Prof Flynn is a great lecturer and is really enthusiastic about the topic of municipal finance. You dont have to have a background in economics or any maths to take this course despite there being a focus on property tax caluculation throughout the course and on the final exam. Great prof, super helpful, lots of office hours!

She is great - very clear lectures and clear expectations. Assignments are not standard but the tas and her provide feedback that is every helpful and you will have room to sharpen up your skills. ppts are quite empty, mostly used for guiding her lectures so not good study material. But the relevant readings in the text :) are actually relevant.

Professor Flynn is amazing! She really opened my eyes to what city politics actually is and how it directly affects us. She also brought in great guest speakers, and regularly engaged with the class by asking good questions to generate discussion, and asking for feedback on lectures. I HIGHLY recommend taking her city politics class!!
